cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with image-to-image translation, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves semantic matching and self-supervised learning, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of non-local blocks, which are commonly used in graph-related problems (cs.GR), and a multi-task architecture, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
